  "local_port": 45898,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I recently wrote a Hindi poetry on indo pak tension . how can I take it to prime minister.?",
  "response": "Sharing your Hindi poetry on Indo-Pak tension directly with the Prime Minister of India is a commendable initiative. Here are some steps you can take to ensure your message reaches the Prime Minister:\n\n### 1. **Social Media Platforms**\n   - **Twitter**: Tag the Prime Minister\u2019s official Twitter handle (@narendramodi) and use relevant hashtags like #PMOIndia, #IndoPakRelations, or #\u0939\u093f\u0902\u0926\u0940\u0915\u093e\u0935\u094d\u092f to increase visibility.\n   - **Instagram**: Share your poetry on Instagram and tag the official PMO India account (@pmohindia) or Narendra Modi\u2019s personal account (@narendramodi).\n   - **Facebook**: Post your poetry on Facebook and tag the official PMO India page or Narendra Modi\u2019s page.\n\n### 2. **Write a Letter**\n   - Send a physical letter to the Prime Minister\u2019s Office (PMO) along with your poetry. Address it as follows:\n     ```\n     To,  \n     The Prime Minister of India,  \n     Prime Minister\u2019s Office,  \n     South Block, Raisina Hill,  \n     New Delhi - 110011  \n     ```\n   - Keep the letter concise and respectful, explaining the purpose of your poetry and why you\u2019re sharing it.\n\n### 3. **Email to PMO**\n   - Send an email to the PMO at **connect@mygov.in** or **pmosb@pmo.nic.in**. Attach your poetry as a PDF or include it in the email body. Write a brief, respectful introduction.\n\n### 4. **Submit via MyGov**\n   - MyGov is the Government of India\u2019s citizen engagement platform. You can submit your poetry through the MyGov website ([https://www.mygov.in/](https://www.mygov.in/)) under the \u201cSubmit Your Ideas\u201d section.\n\n### 5. **Reach Out Through MPs or Local Representatives**\n   - Contact your local Member of Parliament (MP) or a representative who can forward your poetry to the PMO. They often have direct channels to the Prime Minister\u2019s Office.\n\n### 6. **Publish Your Poetry**\n   - Consider publishing your poetry in Hindi newspapers, magazines, or online platforms like *Amar Ujala*, *Dainik Jagran*, or *Navbharat Times*. This can increase its visibility and may catch the attention of the PMO.\n\n### 7. **Leverage Poetry Communities**\n   - Share your poetry on platforms dedicated to Hindi literature, such as **Kavita Kosh** or **Rekhta**. These platforms have a large audience and may help amplify your voice.\n\n### 8. **Use Creative Visuals**\n   - Create a video or audio rendition of your poetry and share it on YouTube, Instagram, or other platforms. Tag the PMO or use relevant hashtags to increase its reach.\n\n### 9. **Contact PMO Directly**\n   - Call the PMO helpline (+91-11-23016857) and inquire about the best way to share your poetry. Be polite and concise when explaining your request.\n\n### 10. **Use Influence of Public Figures**\n   - If you know any public figures, writers, or influencers who support your cause, ask them to share your poetry or amplify your message.\n\nRemember to remain respectful and patient, as the PMO receives a large volume of messages daily. Best of luck in sharing your heartfelt poetry!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
